   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Guidelines and protocol 
2. Stakeholder mapping and engagement plan 
3. A report on the existing capacities and skills, and a gap analysis 
4. Training Modules and Training of Trainers 
5. Stocktaking report on climate information for adaptation planning 
6. Draft National Adaptation Plan</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2019">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Scattered policies and organizational mandates, impacting CCA in different ways.
2. Unclear understanding of skills necessary for CCA policy decision making.
3. Government and official staff not trained in scientific  and technical skills for CCA decision making.
4. No comprehensive list of all adaptation related actions in country.
5. Activities in parallel on similar themes with organizations working on SDGs.
6. Disjointed information and knowledge database, the collective knowledge is not creating a complete picture of climate change or adaptation at a national level in Bhutan. 
7. Scientific CC knowledge not produced locally, and not scaled at all appropriate levels.
8. No sector specific adaptation information
9. Water resources lacking the appropriate strategy for CCA.
10. No method to cost CCA projects.
11. No existing NAP draft.
12. NAP&#x2019;s implementation strategy not created.
13. Relevant agencies and divisions unaware of the NAP and its contents. 
14. Limited GPMS system to track progress, but not for CCA specifically.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2019-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2019-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Draft guideline and protocol to facilitate process for planners and anyone else engaged in the NAP formulation developed

2. Stocktaking report on climate information for adaptation planning as part of draft NAP protocol developed

3. Mapping and assessment of existing capacities and skills on climate change adaptation including a gap analysis</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Draft guideline and protocol available
2. Stocktaking report completed
3. SDG- NAP- NKRA (National Key Results Areas) linkages mapped
4. Capacity and skills gap assessment report, and strategy for capacity development completed.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Training modules developed
2. Long term research strategy on climate adaptation developed
3. Sectorial vulnerability and impact assessment developed</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	Training modules for climate integration at RIM being developed, draft modules available
2.	Climate research strategy and roadmap developed
3.	Sectorial vulnerability assessments ongoing, first draft reports available.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Participate in NAP expo to share lessons/good practices and conduct Vulnerability &amp; Risk Assessment training to TWG members
2. Roll out climate integrated modules in Post Graduate courses in RIM
3. Establish climate platform and protocol for sharing information/data
4. Complete Climate change risk assessments for water, agriculture, forests &amp; biodiversity, and health
5. Design climate training program and train RUB faculty and field-based professionals for roll out of short term trainings in 2022
6. Develop CCA screening guidelines and train relevant agencies in using the guidelines</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
    </period>
